<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>Medtronic (MDT)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Medtronic plc. — using recent financials, disclosed assumptions, and one final number.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV !== null ? roundedIV.toFixed(2) : 'N/A'}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${currentPrice !== null ? currentPrice.toFixed(2) : 'N/A'} ({marginOfSafety !== null ? marginOfSafety : 'N/A'}%)</div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${ttmRevenue !== null ? (ttmRevenue / 1000).toFixed(1) + 'B' : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">TTM Revenue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${fcfBase !== null ? (fcfBase / 1000).toFixed(1) + 'B' : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">TTM Free Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${ttmEPS !== null ? ttmEPS.toFixed(2) : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">TTM EPS (Diluted)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{ttmOpInc !== null && ttmRevenue !== null && ttmRevenue !== 0 ? ((ttmOpInc / ttmRevenue) * 100).toFixed(1) + '%' : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${netCash !== null ? (netCash / 1000).toFixed(1) + 'B' : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model — the gold standard of intrinsic valuation. No multiples, no comparables, no vibes. Just future cash flows discounted to today.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>Medtronic generated <strong>${fcfBase !== null ? (fcfBase / 1000).toFixed(2) : 'N/A'} billion</strong> in trailing twelve months (TTM) free cash flow. This is real cash the business produces after paying for necessary capital expenditures and operations.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We project FCF to grow at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(0)}% per year</strong> for 5 years. This reflects Medtronic's position as a mature, stable medical device manufacturer with consistent but single-digit growth potential driven by aging demographics and product innovation.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}% forever</strong>. This captures long-term inflation and modest population growth, aligning with global GDP expectations.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>Future cash flows are discounted at <strong>{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(0)}%</strong>. Medtronic's low beta indicates lower volatility than the broader market. With a 10Y Treasury yield of 4.18%, an 8% cost of capital provides an appropriate risk premium for this dividend aristocrat.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
      <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash (${netCash !== null ? (netCash / 1000).toFixed(2) : 'N/A'}B) = Equity Value. Divide by shares outstanding ({sharesOutstanding !== null ? (sharesOutstanding / 1000).toFixed(2) : 'N/A'}B) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
  <p>A DCF is highly sensitive to its inputs. Here's what we chose and why.</p>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(0)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Medtronic has experienced slow-to-moderate top-line growth. While new product cycles (like Hugo robotics and diabetes care) offer catalysts, the law of large numbers and competitive pressures keep sustainable medium-term growth in the mid-single digits.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(0)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        10Y Treasury: 4.18%. As a defensive healthcare stock with highly predictable cash flows and low macroeconomic cyclicality, Medtronic commands a lower cost of capital than high-growth tech or cyclical industrials. 8% represents a solid required return.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        A long-term growth rate of 2.5% reflects perpetual healthcare spending increases, inflation, and pricing power. It is intentionally conservative, ensuring we do not over-rely on terminal value inflation to justify the current price.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
